Model:Attribute.name: isBinaryA
Model:Attribute.annotation: True, if the association is binary. False if it is ternary or of higher order.

Model:Attribute.name: isMultipleA
Model:Attribute.annotation: True, if and only if the upper bound of the multiplicity is greater than one. Since there is nothing like a max. size for a collection in OCL, the exact value of the upper bound is not relevant.

Model:Attribute.name: isOrderedA
Model:Attribute.annotation: True, if and only if the multivalued collection of elements constrained by this Multiplicity is sequentially ordered. If the collection is not multivalued, this attribute has no meaning.

Model:Attribute.name: isUniqueA
Model:Attribute.annotation: True, if and only if the elements in the collection constrained by this Multiplicity are unique, i.e. the collection is a set. If the collection is not multivalued, this attribute has no meaning.

Model:Attribute.name: isInstanceLevelA
Model:Attribute.annotation: True, if this is an instance level feature. False, if it is a classifier level feature.
